Reasoning: The paper analyzes citation cascades in blog networks, which involves social interactions and information spreading. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the study of social networks and data analysis. cs.SOC is also a likely category as it focuses on social networks and their impact on society. cs.IR and cs.CL are less likely categories as they are more focused on natural language processing and information retrieval, which are not the main focus of this paper.
